# Dispatch scope (supersedes operations user id)

**On-demand rule.** Mission Control warm-up loads [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/rules/bootstrap.mdc`](bootstrap.mdc) as the sole R&D `alwaysApply: true` bootstrap. Read **this file** when you need **`dispatchId`**, **`operationsDocsDirectory`**, or DbOnly terminal dispatch binding ‚Äî not on every dispatch warm-up.

Normative hosting layout: [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/0_hosting-repo.mdc`](.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/0_hosting-repo.mdc) ¬ß **Operations storage phases**, ¬ß **Dispatch persistence (DbOnly terminal)**, and ¬ß **Plans (dispatch-scoped discovery)**.

---

## Agent dispatch scope (binding)

Every Mission Control agent lane on a dispatch is bound to **one dispatch scope**:

| Field | Source | Agent use |
|-------|--------|-----------|
| **`dispatchId`** | Warm-up / spawn preamble (**Active dispatch UUID**) | Stable dispatch identity; never infer from epoch folder name alone |
| **`operationsDocsDirectory`** | Warm-up / spawn preamble (absolute path) | Write operational docs **only** under this directory |
| **Slot id** | Lane identity block | Lane identity for this agent; spawn handover via DB + MCP |

**Forbidden:**

- Constructing `.sedea/operations/.../` or `.sedea/operations/joint/...` paths for lane work
- Constructing or depending on `.sedea/operations/**/dispatch/**` paths for entity IO
- **`ls -lt`** (or any mtime sort) across all dispatch folders under `.sedea/operations/`
- Inferring dispatch scope from ‚Äúnewest‚Äù folder, parallel tabs, or PR index alone without **`targetPlanSlug`** + active **`dispatchId`**

Refresh host identity with MCP **`sedea_get_current_user`** when a skill requires it ‚Äî **not** to derive operations filesystem paths.

