## Customer migration (legacy scope ‚Üí workspace-bound layout)

**Prerequisite ‚Äî worktree quiescence (binding):** Before running the migration script, reach **zero active git worktrees** on the hosting repo (close or merge in-flight PR worktrees, remove stale worktree directories). Active worktrees hold plan sidecars and absolute paths tied to the pre-migration layout.

From **`HOSTING_ROOT`**:

```bash
# 1. Dry-run first (recommended)
node .sedea/centers/sedea/scripts/migrate-operations-bundle-layout.mjs --dry-run

# 2. Execute when dry-run summary looks correct
node .sedea/centers/sedea/scripts/migrate-operations-bundle-layout.mjs
```

| Flag | Effect |
|------|--------|
| `--dry-run` | Report moves/rewrites without filesystem changes |
| `--force` | Override worktree preflight (discouraged) |
| `--hosting-root PATH` | Hosting repo root (default: walk up from `$PWD`) |

The script: preflights `git worktree list`, merges legacy scope trees (`user`, `joint`, other UUID segments) into the workspace-bound scope, rewrites in-file path strings under `.sedea/operations/`, and prints a JSON summary. Re-run is idempotent.

**After migration:** commit `.sedea/operations/` in the operations git repo if applicable; reopen dispatches via Mission Control using **`dispatchId`** + MCP / DB binding (not path segment construction).

